                                         CAPE TOWN - Hawks investigators have arrested a man who was found with drugs worth an estimated R1.8 million in the Eastern Cape.  The 45-year-old suspect was apprehended at his flat on Saturday during a joint operation between the Hawks and crime intelligence officers.  They found Tik, cocaine and crack on the premises.  Hawks spokesperson Anelisa Feni says, “They found the drugs in a safe in his bedroom and bathroom sink. Officials also found case worth R12,500.” (Edited by Zamangwane Shange)